content: Today I will tell you the last part of Japanese old tournament" top ten league"
If you joined last my lesson, you would know. however, I will tell you that tournament again.
Top ten league started 1974, and continued 7 years.
Today I will introduce you the 2nd year.
Probably you know, Mr. Isobe won the 1st year at the 9-0 score!
At that time, Isobe was treated as a God more than Ando or Nakamura.
Because noboday beat him at that time.
However, this year had changed the renju history.
Isobe lost many games and lost the God position.
oh, who broke the wall first?
Today I will tell you from 6 rounds.
Before that, I will tell you the situation the tournament until 5th rounds.

Until 5rounds of top ten league
Isobe 5-0
Nakamura 4-1
Hayakawa 3-2
Kobayashi 3-2
Inoue 3-2
Nishimura 2-3
Yamazaki 2-3
Sakashita 2-3
Mitsumori 1-4
Shibata 0-5
Nakamura lost against Nishimura so far.
You know Hayakawa, Mitsumori, Nakamura, Nishimura, don't you?
Mr. Sakashita will attend 2004 meijinsen tournament instead by Nishimura.
They are keeping renju and strength.
I must say Mr. Isobe won the 14games in a row from the 1st year.
Now I will introduce Isobe's lost game first.
Kobayashi was black, Isobe was white.
But I think black played very well.
At that time  9th move is most natural.
tactics is VCT or VCF threat
sorry GM,14 which type of threat?
I don't know but not so strong.
This variation is also popular in Japan at that time.
Which protection do you prefer, K7 or G11?
At that time, I believe G11 was more popular.
Because we didn't find good attacking for white.
At that time, people believed 10, 12 combination were the best.
It is not VCF but white can not attack.
Nishimura won with this variation by white after that, he was smart!

and he dominated renju for so many years
